    IComponent, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IFIXSource, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, ICatalysEventListener, Cloneable, EventListener

    public class BurstOrderEntryProcessor
extends FIXSourceListenerBase
    Burst order entry message processor.

    This is a simple message processor designed to simulate order flows into the market. It has the following capabilities:

    • Send a trickle of new order single messages at a configurable rate
    • Send a burst of new order single messages at a configurable rate
    • Cancel all active orders at a configurable rate.

    Configuration example: <SourceMessageProcessors> <GenericProcessor class="com.camerontec.catalys.server.test.BurstOrderEntryProcessor" id="SourceBurstOrderEntry"> <Properties id="BurstOrderEntryProperties"> <Property name="symbol" value="ASX"/> <Property name="numBurstMsgs" value="1000"/> <Property name="burstInterval" value="600000"/> <Property name="burstOffset" value="10000"/> <Property name="numTrickleMsgs" value="1"/> <Property name="trickleInterval" value="5000"/> <Property name="msgSendInterval" value="0"/> <Property name="cancelInterval" value="600000"/> <Property name="cancelOffset" value="100000"/> </Properties> </GenericProcessor> </SourceMessageProcessors> <ListenerMessageProcessors> <GenericProcessor class="com.camerontec.catalys.server.test.BurstOrderEntryProcessor" id="ListenerBurstOrderEntry" refid="SourceBurstOrderEntry"/> </ListenerMessageProcessors>

    This message processor sets the storeMessages attribute to false to enable message reuse.
